Heat the butter in a pan, add the garlic and fry for one minute.Add the asparagus, peas, soya beans and spinach and stir fry for 1-2 minutes, until the spinach has wilted slightly.Add the pasta and a little of the cooking water to the pan and stir to combine.Stir in the lemon juice and zest and the herbs and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, divide the pasta among four bowls, sprinkle over the hazelnuts and parmesan shavings and drizzle with olive oil.